+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
|     Python Cheatsheet  |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Variables and Data     | Operators                               |
| Types                  |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Variable assignment:   | Arithmetic operators:                   |
| variable_name = value  | +, -, *, /, %, **                       |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Common data types:     | Comparison operators:                   |
| int, float, str, bool,| ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=                    |
| list, tuple, dict     |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Control Flow           | Functions                               |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Conditional statements:| Defining a function:                     |
| if, elif, else        | def function_name(parameters):           |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Looping constructs:   | Returning values:                        |
| for, while            | return                                  |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Lists                  | Strings                                 |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Creating a list:       | Creating a string:                       |
| my_list = [item1,     | my_string = 'Hello, World!'              |
| item2, item3]        |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Accessing elements:    | String concatenation:                    |
| my_list[index]        | string1 + string2                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Modifying elements:    | String methods:                          |
| my_list[index] =      | upper(), lower(), split(),                |
| new_value             | strip(), replace()                       |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| List methods:          |                                        |
| append(), extend(),   |                                        |
| insert(), remove(),   |                                        |
| pop()                |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Dictionaries           | Error Handling                          |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Creating a dictionary: | Handling exceptions:                     |
| my_dict = {'key1':   | try, except, finally                     |
| value1, 'key2':      |                                        |
| value2}             | Raising exceptions:                      |
|                      | raise Exception('Error message')          |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Accessing values:     |                                        |
| my_dict['key']       |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Modifying values:     |                                        |
| my_dict['key'] =    |                                        |
| new_value             |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Dictionary methods:   |                                        |
| keys(), values(),    |                                        |
| items()              |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| File Handling          | Modules and Packages                     |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Opening a file:        | Importing a module:                      |
| file = open('filename',| import module_name                       |
| 'mode')              |                                        |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Reading file content:  | Importing specific                       |
| content = file.read() | functions/classes:                       |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Writing to a file:     | from module_name import                  |
| file.write('content') | function_name                            |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
| Closing a file:        | Creating your own module:                |
| file.close()          | Save code in a .py file and import it    |
+------------------------+----------------------------------------+
